h2 SASS

p.-text Chi defines colors with Sass language variables.

.-mb--4
  :code(lang='sass')
    $colorscheme: (
      grey: (
        100: #242526,
        90: #313336,
        80: #3f4145,
        70: #53565a,
        60: #72767a,
        50: #8e9399,
        40: #acb0b5,
        30: #d0d4d9,
        20: #edf0f2,
        10: #f8f9f9,
      )
    );

p.-text A utility function has been created to reference them.

.-mb--4
  :code(lang='sass')
    set-color($scheme, $tone)

p.-text
  | To use it, add chi through npm and import the variables and
  | mixins sass files.

.-mb--4
  :code(lang='sass')
    @import '@centurylink/chi/src/chi/_variables';
    @import '@centurylink/chi/src/chi/_mixins';

    .example {
      color: set-color(grey, 60);
    }
